================================================================================
Bundled WCAG 2.2 dataset (the worldwide core)
================================================================================

The file src/data/wcag.json is derived from the official Web Content Accessibility
Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 source published by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C).

Source: https://github.com/w3c/wcag  (guidelines/ success-criterion fragments)
Spec:   https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/

WCAG 2.2 is © W3C and is reused here under the W3C Document License
(https://www.w3.org/copyright/document-license/). ultra11y reproduces only the
success-criterion ids, titles and conformance levels (the Level A + AA subset),
adding its own engine-specific fields (rule coverage, automatability class). It
does not reproduce the normative prose. Attribution: « WCAG 2.2 — W3C ».

================================================================================
Bundled RGAA standards pack (France)
================================================================================

The files src/data/standards/rgaa.json and src/data/standards/rgaa.glossary.json
are the RGAA standards pack, derived from the official Référentiel Général
d'Amélioration de l'Accessibilité (RGAA), version 4.1.2, published by the
Direction interministérielle du numérique (DINUM / DISIC) of the French government.

Source: https://github.com/DISIC/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr
        (RGAA/criteres.json, RGAA/glossaire.json)

The RGAA content is published under the Licence Ouverte / Open License 2.0
(Etalab): https://www.etalab.gouv.fr/licence-ouverte-open-licence/

ultra11y restructures this content into a standards pack (composing dotted
criterion ids, deriving plain-text titles, mapping each criterion to bare WCAG
success-criterion ids, stripping glossary HTML) but does not alter its meaning.
Attribution: « RGAA 4.1.2 — DINUM ».

================================================================================
Bundled RGAA implementation guidance
================================================================================

The file src/data/guidance/rgaa.json is an implementation-guidance dataset: short
derived summaries and minimal before/after code examples, each keyed to an RGAA
criterion and the WCAG success criteria it maps onto. Its entry ids mirror the rule
files of the SocialGouv/skills "rgaa-html-css" skill, and the patterns are adapted
from that skill and the official RGAA méthode (DINUM).

Source: https://github.com/SocialGouv/skills (skills/rgaa-html-css/rules)
        https://accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr/methode/criteres-et-tests/

The underlying RGAA criteria are © DINUM under the Licence Ouverte / Etalab 2.0
(above). ultra11y stores only short derived summaries + minimal illustrative
examples, not verbatim prose. When ingesting another rule source, record its own
license and attribution in the dataset header and in this NOTICE before
redistributing any of its text. Attribution: « RGAA 4.1.2 — DINUM ; patterns adaptés
de SocialGouv/skills ».

================================================================================
Inspiration
================================================================================

The audit report format is inspired by the RGAA audit conventions of DINUM and
the etalab-ia/skills RGAA skill; the native-HTML-first authoring rules are
adapted from the SocialGouv/skills rgaa-html-css skill. No source code was
copied from either project; only public conventions and rule lists were adapted.
